DRUG ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE; FLU LIKE SYMPTOMS; OFF LABEL USE; This spontaneous report received from a physician concerned a 16 year old female. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's pre-existing medical conditions included no known allergies. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 042A21A, and expiry: 21/JUN/2021) dose was not reported, administered on 03-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. No concomitant medications were reported. On 03-APR-2021, the subject experienced drug administered to subject of inappropriate age. On 03-APR-2021, the subject experienced flu like symptoms. On 03-APR-2021, the subject experienced off label use. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from flu like symptoms on 04-APR-2021, and the outcome of drug administered to patient of inappropriate age and off label use was not reported. This report was non-serious.; Sender's Comments: V0: Medical assessment comment was not required as per standard procedure as case assessed as non-serious.

16 2021-06-30 fatigue SUSPECTED CLINICAL VACCINATION FAILURE; SUSPECTED COVID-19 INFECTION; INAPPROPRIATE AGE AT VACCINE A... Read more
Close
SUSPECTED CLINICAL VACCINATION FAILURE; SUSPECTED COVID-19 INFECTION; INAPPROPRIATE AGE AT VACCINE ADMINISTRATION; SORENESS IN THE ARM; TIRED AT NIGHT; This spontaneous report received from a parent concerned a 16 year old female. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient was diagnosed with Lyme disease when she was 10 or 11 years old but no after effects and she is fine now. The patient have just seasonal allergies. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 1805018, expiry: UNKNOWN) dose was not reported, 1 total, administered to the left arm on 12-MAY-2021 (coded as inappropriate age at vaccine administration) for prophylactic vaccination. No concomitant medications were reported. After vaccination, the patient had soreness in the arm for a couple of days and felt tired at night which cleared in 24-48 hours. The patient work at a camp, where somebody came down with Covid and there have been couple of cases of Covid-19. The patient exhibited symptoms of Covid and was tested by rapid test on 13-JUN-2021, which was negative. Laboratory data included: SARS-CoV-2 test (NR: not provided) negative. The patient was subsequently tested twice on 14-JUN-2021, both positive (suspected clinical vaccination failure and suspected covid-19 infection). The patient's father did not know the specifics of the tests that were done. The patient was quarantined in the camp and was till under quarantine in the camp. The patient also presented with Covid symptoms such as Covid cough and pain in the chest for coughing. The patient felt fine now (as reported). The patient's father mentioned that the camp had to make a report to the health authorities but did not think that the patient visited a physician. Laboratory data included SARS-CoV-2 test (NR: not provided) positive. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from soreness in the arm, and tired at night on 14-MAY-2021, and the outcome of suspected covid-19 infection, suspected clinical vaccination failure and inappropriate age at vaccine administration was not reported. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition). This case is associated with the Product quality complaint (PQC): 90000184104.; Sender's Comments: V0 - 20210660267- COVID-19 VACCINE AD26.COV2.S -Suspected clinical vaccination failure. This event(s) is considered not related. The event(s) has a compatible/suggestive temporal relationship, is unlabeled, and has unknown scientific plausibility. There are other factors more likely to be associated with the event(s) than the drug. Specifically: SPECIAL SITUATIONS

My hands and feet went numb and I started sweating all over. After resting my head on the table for about 10 minutes I felt better and was able to move to a cot where I rested for another 20 minutes or so until I felt pretty much back to normal. I was treated by the medical team at the site who cleared me to go home.

Chills, shortly followed by shivering and chattering. The shivering is so intense it essentially renders the patient in a state of involuntary writhing; muscles across the body, even if not in movement, may be tensed to the point of pain. Muscles affected lie in the legs, arms, and torso. An observer might mistake the event for a seizure, though the patient is fully conscious for the duration. The episode lasts only a few minutes; such an episode has only occurred once.

18 2021-04-15 fever, chills, fatigue, influenza like illness She got her J & J vaccine around 4:30 on April 7th ,2021. She was feeling fine up until around 10:0... Read more
Close
She got her J & J vaccine around 4:30 on April 7th ,2021. She was feeling fine up until around 10:00 that night when she began to have some of the regular side effects in addition to some unusual ones that were more concerning. She had chills was feverish and nauseous with flu like symptoms of her body aching. However, at around 10:30 that night she reported having difficulty breathing and having chest pains with pain when she would take breaths. She noticeably was taking very small but frequent breaths due to the pain. She described a pressure on her chest as if there was a bowling ball sitting on top of her chest. She was crying from the pain and her difficulty breathing. She also reported that her throat felt like it was smaller/ constricted. At that time, she was given Acetaminophen and later around 12:00 she was given Benadryl. When she went to bed that night, she was in pain but she also reported that her heart was racing and her resting pulse at the time was 110 bpm. She had the flu like symptoms into Thursday evening but by Friday she looked a lot better except for her difficulty breathing with complaints of chest pain when she breaths with continued pressure on her chest. She rested in bed for most of Friday and on Saturday she got dressed in the afternoon and took a walk around half a mile at which time she was exhausted and felt out of breath. When she walked back from her destination about a half mile, she needed to rest in bed to recuperate. The pain while breathing lasted into Sunday. Monday morning, she attempted to run and became winded from running a short distance of ¼ of the block and could not catch her breath having difficulty breathing and throwing up with a lot of subsequent chest pain that day. She was taken to the doctor by 10:00 that morning to run lab tests and get an examination. She is slowly getting better and taking it easy but Tuesday she still had some pain and by Thursday she is reporting that while the chest pain is still there it is more of a discomfort that she feels when breathing as compared to pain. She continues to report the discomfort when breathing till today 4/16/21 and is still limiting her physical activity but going about her daily routine.

She has a history of Bipolar II, dx about 2 years ago. She has been in counseling for the past 5 years. She just changed from effexor to lexapro about 1 month ago. She has been on abilify 10mg for the past ~6months. On 4/8/21 she went to bed around 11pm and awoke on 4/9 around 8:30am. She had her JJ covid vaccine on 4/9/21. She had 2 handfuls of goldfish crackers on the way to her vaccine appointment around 11am. She had ~6-8oz of water when she awoke. She arrived at the Clinic on campus. She sat down for ~5 minutes and then the staff came to get her. She had the shot administered in left deltoid. When she first felt the pain her vision started to go black and she felt like she was going to pass out. She denies feeling hot or dizzy prior to event. Her vision went completely black, then when she "came to" she was bent over in her chair with arms drawn up to body and fists clenched. Immediately her body relaxed and she felt very confused. She was told she just had a seizure - bend forward and had whole body shaking for ~30 seconds. She felt extremely nauseated and had some dry heaving. Someone helped her to the floor and put up her legs. She was told she looked very pale. She felt much better within 5 minutes. Vitals were checked and were stable. She was given granola bar to eat and drank ~12oz of water. No one sided weakness, no incontinence, no tongue bite. She stayed there for ~45 minutes for monitoring. Someone walked her to her car, asked her if she was ok, and then she drove herself home. Of note, the room she was in was warm and they were going to open doors to get some air. She was not ill or tired at the time. After the event she drove for 5 minutes to her home. Once in her room she felt extremely tired and then slept until 7pm (~6-7 hours). She then called Mom. Mom reports that patient sounded different on the phone. Speech was slow and she seemed "off." Mom drove to her and was at her room by around 7:40pm. At that time, patient looked very pale to Mom. Mom took her home, gave her chicken soup. She did not have an appetite. She just wanted to go to sleep. Mom tried to have her stay up until around 10pm. She had ~8oz of water and then went to bed. She slept through the night. She awoke the next morning and reports that her brain felt like it hurt to work. She had chills, body pain, shakiness during the day on 4/10/21. This was easily managed by tylenol q4. Of note, she did have covid19 in 8/2020. She was ill for ~1 week with lack of smell/taste, febrile, shakiness, headache. She had an odd event on 4/19/21 while giving a presentation at school. She had sudden onset of left pinky numbness/tingling with radiated up the side of her forearm. This lasted ~1-2 minutes. However, her left arm hurt for a few hours afterward. She denies any fatigue after event. She has a Mirena IUD. She smokes nicotine via vape numerous times per day. She smoke weed up to 3X/day but not every day. She drinks beer a few days per week.

Around 5:00 PM after having gotten my shot, I arrived home from a drive down to meet my sister. Precautions were taken, masks were worn, safe social distance was maintained and I have no reason to believe any of the symptoms I experienced upon returning home were related to anything other than the vaccine, particularly since first that is how vaccines work and second one of my friends who was vaccinated at the same time as me at the clinic was going through similar pains. It started as a discomfort in my intestines or possibly just below my stomach in general. I thought my pants were too tight but just in case I let my mom take over driving the rest of the way home. When I got to the house, I had about an hour of usable time left before I went into a complete state of delirium. We're not sure how high my fever actually got before my mom woke up and checked in on me at 9:00 PM, but after having pulled the covers away I registered at 102.5° F. I was screaming in a half-awake and half-asleep nightmare, trying to get someone to come help me and unable to get anyone's attention. I would, as a result, like to insist that it be added to recommendations to not be alone after getting the vaccine! For the whole first night! I believe that I genuinely could have died. My brain was melting for lack of more proper medical terminology, and I stopped being able to understand and speak my own first language in an incredibly confused state. This was entirely a result of two simultaneous factors: Fever and Chills. First, the fever made my skin ache. Wearing any clothing hurt. But once I took off my pants in exchange for some breezy shorts, I was covered in goosebumps and feeling frozen even though it was solidly in the 70s. I claimed under blankets and still couldn't get warm enough. The backs of my thighs were insanely hot in comparison to the fronts of them, so I just warmed my body under 3 layers of blankets trying to get the chills to go away. I did that for about four hours during which time I was basically constantly screaming incoherently.

Johnson and johnson covid-19 vaccine eau March 20th - allergic reaction to covid vaccine Johnson & Johnson. Allergic reaction started approximately 2 minutes after receiving shot. It started with itching and redness on my arms and upper chest. After approximately 10 minutes, I knew something was wrong and I signaled an attendant. They immediately brought me over to the EMTs on site, where they looks me over and started drawing up IV Benadryl. In the time it took for them to draw up IV Benadryl and insert the IV, the hives on my chest started to turn into burning and ice sensations intermittently. As soon as they administered the IV Benadryl, the itching redness and hives on my arms went away within a couple minutes, and I was left with only redness on my upper chest. They felt comfortable with me getting a ride to the ER from my dad and not getting emergency transport. At the ER, they gave me pepcid and prednisone. About an hour and a half later, I started developing chest tightness and hives and redness on the side of my face. They decided to administer more Benadryl and start epinephrine. I was discharged a couple hours later. March 22nd - I went back to the hospital, with complaints of severe stomach pain. The stomach pain lasted approximately 24 hours. March 20th to march 26th - I experienced extreme fatigue. I was exhausted to the point where on Wednesday I took a ten minute shower and by the end of it I had to lay down again because I was shaking from exhaustion. Symptoms improved slightly until April 5th where it started taking a turn for the worse. April 5th - I started noticing black spots in my vision that wouldn't go away. They didn't move and they stayed in one spot for hours until I fell asleep and then they'd be gone the next morning. They usually started around 8:00 or 9:00 at night. Sometimes a couple hours earlier. They came every day until Friday April 9th when they did not come. April 5th to present - I also started noticing light-headedness, motion sickness when I stood still or sat in a chair, nausea, neck pain, and periods of muscle weakness in the neck. These symptoms have not stopped. Friday April 9th around 6:45 p.m. I started having a bad migraine, I noticed in the bathroom at work my eyes were dilating over and over and over again rapidly. The pain was very high. I ended up leaving work early and going to the emergency room. While at the emergency room they treated my migraine with a cocktail of Benadryl, toradol, and compazine. It reduced the pain at the time, however it did not take away the migraine. Friday April 9th to present - My migraine has continued from April 9th and is still happening. I have been having severe light sensitivity, sound sensitivity, and trouble reading. The rapid dilation of my eyes stopped April 10th, however my eyes stayed dilated until April 12th. In addition to all of my other symptoms, there are others that I am not as positive are relevant. I have asthma and it has been worse over the past couple of weeks, it it is not usually worse this time of year. I've been also been having quite a bit more light bruising than normal over the past two weeks and over the past one and a half weeks I have noticed red spots all over my skin. I was not sure if these red spots were normal or not because I do have them on occasion however these are darker than normal.

Starting less than 12 hours from the injection, the adverse effects started with a bad headache and light sensitivity. Within an hour the adverse effects evolves to severe chills, fever, body aches, fatigue and nausea. A few hours later all symptoms continued and worsened. Symptoms persisted throughout the night and into the next day resulting in no sleep. The following day ibuprofen was able to manage symptoms enough where patient was able to sleep. Fever decreased, but chills, headache, fatigue, and vomiting continued. Patient was forcefully vomiting bile after not being able to keep anything down. Patient broke capillaries across the face. Extreme tiredness pursued, but symptoms dwindled over the course of three days.

20 2021-05-25 fever, chills Fever, extreme unbearable aches, chills, joint pain
20 2021-05-25 fever, fatigue I feel inclined to file this report in hopes that someone could study how receiving this vaccine aff... Read more
Close
I feel inclined to file this report in hopes that someone could study how receiving this vaccine affected my endometriosis. Please understand that I?m a proponent of vaccination and building herd immunity; however, women?s health is important and we have a right to be AWARE of ALL side effects. I?ve done my best to research this topic and was able to find very few sources on how COVID-19 vaccines impact menstruation. Aside from the lack of statistics, I found forums on social media platforms with women explaining how their menstrual cycles became irregular some way or another. I did experience the common side effects of fever, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, soreness, and fatigue. In addition, I experienced severe cramps, back pain, thigh pain, groin pain, and nerve pain associated with the sciatic and obturator. I?m happy to be vaccinated because my immune system is far from the best, but if I were to have known that I would be unable to walk from the pain radiating from my back, pelvis, and thigh I would?ve opted for Moderna or Pfizer. At this point in time, I would NOT recommend the Janssen vaccine to someone with endometriosis. At that, this vaccine should be nowhere near as political as it is! My healthcare providers should be more willing to validate my symptoms, rather than saving face with the validity of the vaccine. I was told since my menstrual cycle is irregular I must coincidentally be getting my period, BUT I have not experienced any bleeding nor even spotting. I have no idea what the vaccine did to my body, I have no clue why it would induce such severe pain. I?m glad that the ?normal? symptoms have subsided by the second day, but the nerve pain complicates walking long distance or carrying heavy objects. I think I?ll eventually make a full recovery in the upcoming days, but this experience was so frightening. I laid on the floor for hours crying after I vomited up everything I had eaten. I couldn?t sleep because I couldn?t bear to lay down for long durations of time- and by that I mean more than ten minutes. It genuinely felt like I was getting my period, but whatever it was led to no external bleeding. Again, I?m grateful for the scientists who dedicate their lives to such integral work. I just wish I would?ve known about what was internally happening to my body beforehand, I would?ve chosen a different vaccine.

There were no symptoms until much later in the evening. Around 8:30 PM, I felt fatigued. A little later I had chills for about 30 minutes. I also felt very hot and the cold floor was welcoming. I laid on the floor in the bathroom but felt too awful to sit up. Someone found me in the bathroom around 10:00 PM and called campus safety, which came about 20-30 minutes later. She determined that she could not give me medication on the spot and that she had to take me to the hospital. We arrived at the ER around 10:45 PM. The nurses and doctor took my temperature and found I had a 103-degree fever. Because of my pounding headache, I couldn't hear very well. The doctor gave me a shot of 60mg of Toradol at 10:56 PM. He then gave me instructions to alternate tylenol and ibuprofen every 3 hours, increase my fluids, and only do activity as can be tolerated. I left the hospital around 11:25 PM with a huge headache, but better than when I initially walked in.

21 2021-05-23 fever The first symptom I experienced was a high grade fever that reached 103.5 degrees Fahrenheit. The fe... Read more
Close
The first symptom I experienced was a high grade fever that reached 103.5 degrees Fahrenheit. The fever lasted from 2:00pm on May 10th (the day it was administered) until 2:00 am on a May 11th (the early hours of the day after it was administered). Some weakness, as well as muscular soreness in the left arm persisted in the insuring days. The reason why I chose to report my experience is because something that I thought was abnormal happened. On the evening of May 15th, as I was putting on my pajamas, I noticed an irregular mass in my left breast. As I examined it further, I realized that this mass was not there previously and warning shots fired off in my head, immediately. I immediately asked my grandmother to do another examination of my breast, and she confirmed my suspicion that there was a foreign mass located above my nipple in my left breast. It was difficult for me to closely monitor this mass as it was difficult for me to think about it as it triggered emotional distress. I asked my mom to do an examination and she also noted the mass. A little more than a week later, I noticed that the mass shrunk. Since everyone in my family was on edge for nearly a week suspecting that a 21 year old female in their family could possibly have breast cancer, this caused my family to consult my grandmother?s doctor, and have her assistant contact me about what could potentially be happening. Her assistant spoke to me over the phone and communicated that it is important for me to have the mass formally examined and for me to receive a mammogram. She also mentioned that many women who have received the vaccine also noticed irregular lumps in their breasts after receiving the vaccine. I want women in my age range to be aware that they might notice lumps in their breasts after the vaccine and not to experience the same emotional distress of thinking that they have breast cancer when it could be inflammation occurring in their lymph nodes as a result of being administered the Covid vaccine.

The patient's height, and weight were not reported. No past medical history or concurrent conditions were reported. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of administration was not reported, batch number: 201A21A, and expiry: unknown) dose was not reported,1 total, administered on left arm on 08-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. No concomitant medications were reported. On 08-APR-2021 (12 hours post vaccination), the patient experienced fever and felt fine after 2 days. On 18-JUN-2021, the patient experienced cough and head cold. On 19-JUN-2021, the patient experienced loss of taste, and loss of smell. The patient then realized that it could be coronavirus disease (COVID-19) symptoms and took an 'at-home' covid test which came back positive (suspected clinical vaccination failure, suspected covid-19 infection). At the time of report, the patient still had some lingering cold and her loss of taste and smell did not return. She generally felt better at the time of report and had not consulted a health care provider as her symptoms were mild. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from fever on 10-APR-2021, was recovering from suspected covid-19 infection, and the outcome of suspected clinical vaccination failure was not reported. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition). 22 2021-05-25 headache, sweating Episode of apparent vasovagal syncope a few minutes after receiving the vaccine. This was witnessed... Read more
Close
Episode of apparent vasovagal syncope a few minutes after receiving the vaccine. This was witnessed by myself. She appeared to have loss of consciousness and collapsed onto the pavement striking her posterior head on the pavement (fortunately, she did not strike it with great force). She regained consciousness within 2-3 seconds. She had a small "knot" on her posterior scalp, but no break in the skin. No other apparent injury. She initially complained of a headache, but this resolved over the course of about 10 minutes. She initially was mildly diaphoretic and had a rapid pulse and mild hypotension, but these also resolved over the course of several minutes. A chemical ice pack was applied to the posterior scalp and neck. She had a completely normal neurologic and musculoskeletal examination. She was provided oral fluids (water and kool aid) and a snack (chewy granola bar) and kept under close observation by medical personal for about 30 minutes. Transport to the emergency room via ambulance was offered, but declined. Her boyfriend was called and came to drive her home after she had made an apparent complete recovery. Both he and she were extensively counseled regarding signs and symptoms to be on the lookout for that would indicate the need for further medical evaluation and they both expressed complete understanding and agreement. Of note, she reported that she has had episodes of syncope in the past when having blood drawn for laboratory tests, but decided not to disclose this to on site personal prior to the vaccination thinking she would probably not have a problem.

She was diagnosed with vasovagal syncope due to the vaccine. She refused transport to the ER and left of her own accord.

No initial side effects, barely any arm pain, and I felt completely normal and fine for about 8 hours post vaccination. I did not take any medication/fever reducer. To sum up, I had no side effects upon initially receiving the vaccine, side effects set in ~8 hours post-vaccination and overall lasted about 24 hours. I have had no additional side effects other than those reported and have felt well since those subsided.
